description: From Latin trānsmūtāre, from trans + mūtāre.

verbs.description: transmute (third-person singular simple present transmutes, present participle transmuting, simple past and past participle transmuted)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To change, transform or convert one thing to another, or from one state or form to another.
examples: The alchemists tried to transmute base metals to gold.
Did the base metals transmute to gold?
